def create_new_features(xb_keep, mask_keep, feature_dict, feature_names):
    n_samples, n_features = xb_keep.shape[0], len(feature_dict) * 2  # two intrinsic Feature
    new_x = torch.zeros((n_samples, n_features))  
    new_mask = torch.zeros_like(new_x, dtype=torch.bool) 
    for i in range(n_samples):
        feature_values = []
        for feature in feature_names:
            if feature in feature_dict:
                control_diff = np.abs(xb_keep[i, feature_names.index(feature)] - feature_dict[feature]['Controls']) 
                t2dm_diff = np.abs(xb_keep[i, feature_names.index(feature)] - feature_dict[feature]['T2DM'])
                if not mask_keep[i, feature_names.index(feature)]:
                    feature_values.extend([control_diff, t2dm_diff])
                else:
                    feature_values.extend([0, 0])
                    new_mask[i, len(feature_values)-2:len(feature_values)] = True
        new_x[i, :len(feature_values)] = torch.tensor(feature_values)
    return new_x, new_mask

#EqualLenth bin
import numpy as np

def calculate_bounds_and_bins(data, n_bins):
    bounds = []
    bins = []
    for i in range(data.shape[1]):
        column = data[:, i]
        valid_data = column[~np.isnan(column)]
        if len(valid_data) > 0:
            Q1 = np.percentile(valid_data, 25)
            Q3 = np.percentile(valid_data, 75)
            IQR = Q3 - Q1
            upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
            valid_data_clipped = valid_data[valid_data <= upper_bound]
            if valid_data_clipped.size > 0:
                bin_edges = np.linspace(valid_data_clipped.min(), valid_data_clipped.max(), n_bins + 1)
                bins.append(bin_edges)
            else:
                bins.append(None)
            bounds.append((None, upper_bound))
        else:
            bounds.append((None, None))
            bins.append(None)
    return bounds, bins

def apply_bounds_and_bins(data, bounds, bins, missing_value_label=101, upper_bound_label=103):
    processed_data = np.copy(data)
    for i, (bound, bin_edges) in enumerate(zip(bounds, bins)):
        column = data[:, i]
        missing_indices = np.isnan(column)
        
        processed_data[missing_indices, i] = missing_value_label
            
        valid_indices = ~(missing_indices)
        if bin_edges is not None:
            processed_data[valid_indices, i] = np.digitize(column[valid_indices], bin_edges, right=True)-1
    return processed_data

def calculate_intervals(center, bins):
    intervals = []
    for i in range(1, len(bins)):
        positive_interval = (center + bins[i-1], center + bins[i])
        negative_interval = (center - bins[i], center - bins[i-1])
        intervals.append((positive_interval, negative_interval))
    return intervals
corrected_intervals = [calculate_intervals(center, bins) for center, bins in zip(center_list, bins)]
